life expectancy of 0.655 quality-adjusted life-years (QALYs) over a 60-year time 
horizon, compared with MDI (mean [SD], 10.029 [0.133] vs 9.374 [0.076] QALYs). 
ICERs were Can $27,264 per life-year gained and Can $23,797 per QALY for CSII 
compared with MDI. The results were most sensitive to HbA(1c) assumptions.
CONCLUSION: Based on this analysis, CSII may be a cost-effective treatment 
option when compared with MDI in adult patients with type 1 DM in Canada.

